# API Documentation

This directory contains the REST/gRPC APIs for the central server of the HTL-Defense project. 

## Overview

The APIs are designed to facilitate communication between the frontend and the backend services, allowing for efficient data exchange and interaction with the threat analysis functionalities.

## Endpoints

- **GET /api/v1/threats**: Retrieve a list of detected threats.
- **POST /api/v1/threats**: Submit a new threat for analysis.
- **GET /api/v1/agents**: List all registered agents.
- **POST /api/v1/agents**: Register a new agent.

## Usage

To use the APIs, ensure that the server is running and accessible. You can interact with the endpoints using tools like Postman or curl.

## Authentication

Some endpoints may require authentication. Please refer to the authentication section in the main server documentation for more details.

## Error Handling

The APIs will return standard HTTP status codes to indicate the success or failure of requests. Please refer to the documentation for specific error codes and their meanings.

## Contribution

If you would like to contribute to the API development, please follow the contribution guidelines outlined in the project's documentation.